omq.client.proxy

Class Proxymq

  • java.lang.Object
    • omq.client.proxy.Proxymq
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.reflect.InvocationHandler, Remote

    public class Proxymq
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.reflect.InvocationHandler, Remote
    Proxymq class. This class inherits from InvocationHandler, for this reason each proxymq instance has an associated invocation handler. When a method is invoked on a proxymq instance, the method invocation is encoded and dispatched to the invoke method of its invocation handler.
    Author:
    Sergi Toda

        Proxymq Constructor. This constructor uses an uid to know which object will call. It also uses Properties to set where to send the messages
        Parameters:
        uid - The uid represents the unique identifier of a remote object
        clazz - It represents the real class of the remote object. With this class the system can know the remoteInterface used and it can also see which annotations are used
        env - The environment is used to know where to send the messages
